Pre-Game Insights: The Magic have gone 13-5 at home.
The Timberwolves are 9-10 on the road.
The Magic average 11.5 made 3-pointers per game this season, 1.1 fewer makes per game than the Timberwolves allow (12.6).
The Timberwolves are shooting 45.7% from the field, 0.7% lower than the 46.4% the Magic's opponents have shot this season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Franz Wagner is averaging 24.4 points, 5.6 rebounds, 5.7 assists and 1.7 steals for the Magic.
Julius Randle is averaging 19.5 points, 6.9 rebounds and 4.4 assists for the Timberwolves.
The Magic have 6th in the Eastern Conference with 10.9 offensive rebounds per game led by Goga Bitadze averaging 3.0.
The Timberwolves are third in the Western Conference giving up just 107.7 points while holding opponents to 45.6% shooting.
Others: The Magic are missing several key players including Gary Harris, Paolo Banchero, Jalen Suggs, Franz Wagner, and Moritz Wagner due to injuries.
The Timberwolves are also missing Rob Dillingham due to an injury.
